content.text:
Folding a burrito well not only looks neat but also keeps all the fillings securely inside. Here’s a reliable, step‐by‐step method—often called the “tuck and roll”—to help you achieve the perfect wrap:

1. Warm Your Tortilla:  
   Use a large, soft flour tortilla and warm it up for a few seconds in a microwave or on a skillet. A warm tortilla is more pliable and less likely to tear.

2. Lay Out Your Ingredients:  
   Place your tortilla on a flat surface. Arrange your fillings (rice, beans, meat or veggies, salsa, cheese, etc.) in a long line along the center, leaving about 1 to 2 inches from the edges. This gap will give you enough space to fold the sides in neatly.

3. Fold the Bottom Edge:  
   Start by lifting the bottom edge of the tortilla and fold it up over the filling. Make sure you cover most of the filling so that it’s contained but not so tightly that the contents spill out.

4. Fold the Sides:  
   With the bottom edge tucked, bring both the left and right sides inward toward the center. These folds will further secure your fillings within the burrito. Ensure the sides overlap a bit, but don’t overdo it, as you want to keep the overall structure balanced.

5. Rolling It Up:  
   Now, roll the burrito up from the bottom (where you just made the fold). Use your fingers as a guide to ensure a tight roll. As you roll, tug gently on the sides to keep the filling in place. Continue rolling until the entire tortilla forms a compact cylindrical shape.

6. Optional—Toast for Crispiness:  
   For an extra touch, place your folded burrito seam side down on a hot, lightly oiled griddle or skillet for about 1–2 minutes. This not only helps secure the seam but also gives a delightful crispy texture on the exterior.

Tips for Success:
• Don’t Overfill: Less is more. Overfilling makes the burrito hard to fold and more prone to bursting.
• Uniform Fillings: Distribute the fillings evenly so that every bite is balanced.
• Practice: The first few times might feel clumsy, but practice helps you perfect the fold.

By using these steps, you’ll end up with a neatly folded, delicious burrito that holds together well and is easy to eat. Enjoy your creation!
